<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Notes `Satisfaction' With Vienna Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tudjman Notes `Satisfaction' With Vienna Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205095194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0800 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman has expressed 
satisfaction with the Vienna agreement. He was informed about it 
by Mate Granic and Kresimir Zubak upon their return from Vienna. 
Haris Silajdzic, head of the Muslim delegation, described the 
agreement as the most specific step toward peace, the 
implementation of the Washington agreement, and the constitution 
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina federation. President Alija 
Izetbegovic said that the agreement is a good one, but that the 
Muslims will continue to insist on a unitary state and on 
preserving its external borders. 

</TEXT>

