<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Army Protests Croat Cease-Fire Violations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RSK Army Protests Croat Cease-Fire Violations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1105143494 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1105143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jovan Vlajkovic from Okucani] </F>
  [Text] Overnight and yesterday, the Croatian Army on two 
occasions violated the signed agreement in Western Slavonia. 
The first instance occurred yesterday at around 0900, when 
Croatian planes violated the airspace in the region of the 
village of Zagalici, 7 km east of Okucani. The second instance 
occurred in the course of the night, when Croat Army troops in 
the region of the village of Bujici, 4 km northeast of Novska, 
opened small arms fire on the positions of the Serbian Krajina 
army. The command of the 18th Corps of the Serbian Krajina army 
has lodged a sharp protest with the UN Protection Forces and has 
warned of the possible consequences of such conduct by the 
Croatian side. 

</TEXT>

