<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Strike Continues in Seven Hard Coal Mines </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Strike Continues in Seven Hard Coal Mines </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205102294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0812 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 12 May (PAP)--At 0900 today the strike 
continued in only seven hard coal mines, but production is 
likely to be resumed today. A total of 19 mines were on strike 
before 0600; production was halted in 13 others and reduced in 
another six. Miners were still occupying the State Hard Coal 
Agency building, said its deputy chairman, Henryk Chroszcz. 
  Strikes continue in Piast and Brzeszcze mines (Nadwislanska 
hard-coal company) as well as in Jastrzebie, Pniowek, 
Moszczenica, Borynia, and Zofiowka mines (Jastrzebie hard-coal 
company). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

