<DOCNO> FBIS4-55297 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu093_b_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-093 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yordanov Considers Dissolution of Assembly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yordanov Considers Dissolution of Assembly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205181094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1205181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our reporter Zlatina Georgieva has learned that 
National Assembly Chairman Aleksandur Yordanov has prepared a 
decision on discontinuing the prerogatives of the National 
Assembly on the basis of Article 86, Paragraph 1, and in 
connection with Article 64, Paragraph 3, and Article 98, 
Paragraph 1 of the Bulgarian Constitution. The decision has not 
yet been submitted to the National Assembly office. 
  The decision might sound strange, but legal experts in the 
National Assembly pointed out that according to the 
aforementioned articles the National Assembly could adopt such a 
decision and then adopt a special procedure for setting new 
elections, whose date should be fixed by the president of the 
Republic. 
  According to a member of the Radical Democratic Party, of 
which Yordanov also is a member, Yordanov's motives are related 
to the fact that the National Assembly is not adoptingthe 
important economic bills and is thus blocking reform in the 
country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

