<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDS Rejects Idea of Self-Dissolution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDS Rejects Idea of Self-Dissolution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205181394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1205181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After a stormy meeting behind closed doors, the 
parliamentary faction of the Union of Democratic Forces [SDS] 
rejected by a large majority, with four abstentions, the draft 
decision proposed by Edvin Sugarev on the self-dissolution of 
the National Assembly if Professor Berov's cabinet remains in 
power. This draft decision does not conform to the Bulgarian 
Constitution and would deceive the country. This was stated by 
Stefan Savov, chairman of the SDS parliamentary faction, after 
the meeting. 
  The proposal of Aleksandur Yordanov was not discussed 
because 
he withdrew it. Edvin Sugarev described that proposal as a joke. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

