<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic Wants ICO as `Equal' at Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Izetbegovic Wants ICO as `Equal' at Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205191894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1205191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, has sent a letter to U.S. 
President Bill Clinton, Russian President Boris Yeltsin, UN 
Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali, and Jacques Delors, 
chairman of the EU Ministerial Council. In it Izetbegovic 
demands that the Islamic Conference Organization [ICO] be 
included in the liaison group for Bosnia as an equal partner. 
  Turkish President Demirel called President Izetbegovic over 
the phone, congratulating him on reaching an accord to establish 
the Bosniak-Croatian federation. Turkey believes that this is a 
very important step toward peace which should in the future 
engage the Serbian side also, said President Demirel, promising 
that his country would continue to mediate in all initiatives 
and actions that lead toward the end of bloodshed and 
destruction of this country's economic base. 

</TEXT>

