<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic: Serbs To Withdraw From Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Izetbegovic: Serbs To Withdraw From Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1305105194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1305105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Esteemed listeners, we have just received a 
statement from the office of the president of the Presidency. 
  According to reliable information, the aggressor will 
withdraw by tomorrow morning 3 km from the center of Gorazde, 
from both banks of the Drina River. In order to make this 
possible, the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army will temporarily hand over 
the point Mala Biserna to the control of a British unit of the 
UN Protection Force [UNPROFOR]. If the aggressor does not 
comply with the agreement in full, the British have given 
guarantees that the positions on Mala Biserna will be returned 
to the Gorazde defenders at 1200 on 14 May. 
  This offer has been conveyed to our side by the aggressor 
via 
UNPROFOR. Sefid Buljubasic, commander of the Eastern Bosnian 
Operative Group, has informed the General Staff about this 
offer. President Izetbegovic has agreed to the plan since the 
departure of the Serbian aggressor creates the conditions not 
only for the further normalization of life in the enclave, but 
also for the return of the expelled population to the right bank 
of the Drina River. 
  This is contained in a statement from the office of the 
president of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency. 

</TEXT>

