  [Text] Alain Juppe reacted on Thursday to the U.S. Senate's 
vote calling for the lifting of the arms embargo imposed by the 
United Nations against Bosnia. The French foreign minister said 
that it is "almost the worst of all possible solutions." 
Speaking in Washington, where he earlier met Bill Clinton, 
Alain Juppe said that this solution is "not efficient". 

</TEXT>

