<H3> <TI>   SZDSZ Rejects Alliance With Horn-Led MSZP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SZDSZ Rejects Alliance With Horn-Led MSZP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305161694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1100 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Alliance of Free Democrats [SZDSZ] will not 
participate in the next government if the Hungarian Socialist 
Party [MSZP] nominates Chairman Gyula Horn for prime minister. 
Campaign chief Balint Magyar told journalists that if the MSZP 
names the party chairman as candidate for prime minister, they 
will read the message that the Socialists do not want to form a 
coalition with the SZDSZ. 
  The party will accept only an alliance in which it can 
realize its program, SZDSZ Chairman Ivan Petoe said. He added 
that the final word on coalition membership will be pronounced 
by the extraordinary delegates' meeting of the SZDSZ a week 
after the second round of the elections. 

