<F P=103> AU1205105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Prague, May 12 (CTK) -- The Assembly for the 
Republic-Czechoslovak Republican Party (SPR-RSC) said today "it 
must call on Vaclav Havel to immediately resign over the 
international shame which he has caused by the choice of his 
friends and collaboators for important posts" at the 
Presidential Office (KPR). 
  In its statement given to CTK by a member of the 
extreme-right SPR-RSC leadership, Josef Krejsa, the party said 
that in connection with the report by the Supreme Inspection 
Office (NKU) on the KPR's financial management it would also 
