<H3> <TI>   Socialist Leader Horn Leaves Hospital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socialist Leader Horn Leaves Hospital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205120994 Budapest MTI in English 1154 GMT 12 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1205120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, May 12 (MTI) -- Gyula Horn, chairman of 
the Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP), left Borsod county 
hospital in Miskolc in a reassuring condition today, hospital 
director Zoltan Katona told MTI. On May 5, the car carrying 
Horn back to Budapest from an election rally in Miskolc ran into 
a truck parked on road No. 3 between Nyekladhaza and Emod. The 
party chairman suffered a fractured cervical vertebra, a broken 
wrist and a concussion in the crash. 
  Dr. Katona said Horn is in quite a good condition, and he is 
returning to his family in Budapest. He will invariably need 
longer-term outpatient care and must undergo rehabilitation 
treatment, Katona added. Driver Istvan Mosolygo and the other 
passenger Jeno Zsidey have also left the hospital. 

</TEXT>

