<H3> <TI>   Walesa: Chinese Alliance `Would Be Beautiful' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa: Chinese Alliance `Would Be Beautiful' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205145194 Warsaw PAP in English 1149 GMT 12 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1205145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 12 -- President Lech Walesa received the 
Chief of Staff of the Chinese Army General Zhang Wannian on 
Thursday and said "It would be beautiful for Poland" if there 
was a Polish-Chinese alliance. "I am very pleased that I will 
become acquainted with the point of view of a great state, a 
great army on what is happening in Europe," Walesa said. The 
chief of staff of the Polish army, General Tadeusz Wilecki 
attended the meeting. 
  "After these great changes, attempted changes, we are in a 
quite strange and unclear situation," Walesa said, commenting on 
the feeling of insecurity among the countries of central and 
eastern Europe. "It is true that the Soviet Union no longer 
exists but there are other countries which have nuclear weapons 
at their disposal. We are searching for security. We are 
searching for an alliance which could guarantee this security," 
Walesa explained adding that it would be beautiful if there were 
such an alliance with China. 

</TEXT>

