<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Controversy Over Newspaper's New Name </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Controversy Over Newspaper's New Name </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1305103594 Prague CTK in English 0929 GMT 13 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1305103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava May 13 (CTK) -- "Hardly have we started 
to appear and already problems are upon us," the revamped 
SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA (SLOVAK REPUBLIC) complains on its front 
page today. The daily, close to the former premier, Vladimir 
Meciar, used to be published as REPUBLIKA by the News Agency of 
the Slovak Republic (TA SR) but came out on Thursday [12 May] 
with a new name and the old layout. It is published now by the 
Salus limited company, which is co-owned by Meciar's Movement 
for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS). 
  The paper reports that Pavol Weiss, a leader of the Liberal 
Party, has lodged a complaint with the General Prosecutor's 
Office to investigate whether the paper has committed the 
criminal act of public defamation of the republic by its new 
name. At the same time, the culture minister has asked the 
publisher to change the name, although the abuse of the state 
name is only theoretical. 
  On May 12, TA SR Director General Ivan Melichercik said that 
REPUBLIKA was originally intended to be purely a news agency 
paper but owing to its marked political bias it became 
"incompatible with the fundamental principles of a news agency". 
  From the beginning of its existence REPUBLIKA "dragged a 
boulder of debts behind it"; this contradicted TA SR's legally 
defined status as a public corporation, which is not permitted 
any loss-making entrepreneurial activity. "TA SR's divorce from 
REPUBLIKA proceeds solely from these premises," Melichercik 
stated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-55386 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu093__a94031" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-093-A </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 May 1994 </DATE1>

