  [Text] Tirana, May 10 (ATA) -- The ten accused Albanians on 
the charges of "conspiracy in subversive activity" in the 
Republic of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] will continue to stay in detention, because their 
trial planned for May 9 was postponed, reports Albanian TV, 
according to the information from Skopje. The reason for the 
postponement of the trial for the second time is the 
continuation of attorneys' strike. The trial will start on May 
23. In the Albanian opinion prevails the idea that this is a 
fabricated case were facts are missing to verify their charges. 

