<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rights Council Details Serb Military Exercises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rights Council Details Serb Military Exercises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005163094 Tirana ATA in English 1018 GMT 10 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1005163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 10 (ATA) -- Large units of Serbian 
military forces have engaged in a series of military exercises 
in the villages of Dubovc, Galice, and Mikushnice of Vushtrri, 
apparently to train troops for combat in populated areas, 
according to reports of the Council for the Defence of Human 
Rights and Freedoms from Prishtina. Mass concentrations of 
Serbian military forces and their movement have created a tense 
situation in the above said villages and regions around, because 
Serbian soldiers are also using fire weapons during the 
exercises. 
  The "Azem Bejtja" School yard in Dubovc, its grounds as well 
as the territories of the former mine have turned into areas 
mined by the Serbian soldiers, creating hazards for the 
Albanians residing in these areas. Situations of this kind have 
also been created in Skenderaj, with dozens of Serbian soldiers 
and their dogs standing in front of the houses of Mikushice's 
inhabitants shooting incessantly with fire weapons. 
  The Council for the Defence of Human Rights and Freedoms 
also 
reports that about 300 Serbian troops have engaged in military 
exercises with mechanised means in Sibovc of the Podujeve 
commune. Military concentrations have been noticed recently also 
in Necavc, near Hani i Elezit, with soldiers openly provoking 
Albanians and grabbing their cattle. 
  The mass concentrations of military troops and their 
engagement in exercises show of an escalation of military 
tension, besides that of the police, which are of dangerous 
consequences not only for the inhabitants of the said areas but 
also of the areas beyond. This also testifies to the fact that 
now, with the Kosova question being on the agenda of the 
international organisations to solve it through peaceful ways, 
Belgrade is determined to follow the track of war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

