  [Text] Laszlo Juhasz, news director for Hungarian 
television and head of the election programs office, has 
resigned. He informed Deputy Chairman Gabor Nahlik of his 
decision on 7 May, one day before the first round of the 
National Assembly elections. Nahlik accepted the resignation. 
Laszlo Juhasz recalled that last November he accepted the 
position of director of news only temporarily, until the 
conclusion of the National Assembly elections. 

