<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Joint Chiefs Office Begins Operating </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarajevo Joint Chiefs Office Begins Operating </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505182594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1505182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In keeping with the guidelines issued by Army 
General Rasim Delic, chief of the General Staff of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, and Major General Milivoj Petkovic, the 
commander of the Main Headquarters of the Croatian Defense 
Council [HVO], the joint chiefs of staff in Sarajevo, headed by 
Corps General Ante Roso and Brigadier [words indistinct] 
officially started working today, [word indistinct] the press 
center of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army. 
  During the transitional period, until the federation is 
established, the joint chiefs of staff will have the task of 
setting up a unified armed force of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The work on setting up joint armed forces 
has been progressing in line with the existing military 
agreements and the political concept outlined by the Washington 
Agreement, as well as by the federal agreement signed in Vienna 
recently. 

</TEXT>

