<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Clash with UNPROFOR Unit Near Maglaj </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Clash with UNPROFOR Unit Near Maglaj </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505184494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1505184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Maglaj a general alert was sounded at about 1200 
as the aggressor fired several artillery shells at the town. 
Fortunately, there were no civilian casualties. At the same 
time, Britsh UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] soldiers clashed 
with the Serbian aggressor. 
  [Reporter Hajrudin Ceric] First, the British were caught in 
fierce sniper fire from the criminals on the slopes of Mount 
Ozren. To protect their lives they returned fire from the 
small-caliber guns mounted on their combat vehicles. This was 
no convincing reason for the aggressor to cease fire. On the 
contrary, they opened up with brief but fierce bursts of fire 
from a Bofors gun. There was not the slightest trace of NATO 
aircraft in the sky as the blue helmets were stranded in dire 
straits. We have unofficially learned that there are no 
casualties among the ranks of the UNPROFOR unit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

