<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs: Muslims Continuing Attacks in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs: Muslims Continuing Attacks in Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505195594 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1949 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1505195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Bileca, May 15 (TANJUG) -- The Moslem Army continues 
on Sunday to violate the cease-fire in the area of the eastern 
town of Gorazde, opening fire on the adjacent Serb villages. 
Bosnian Serb Army sources inform that the Moslems on the left 
bank of the Drina [River] have shelled the villages on the right 
bank, where the Serb population has returned after their 
liberation in a Serb counter-offensive which checked a Moslem 
offensive launched from Gorazde earlier this Spring. 
  The Moslem infantry on Sunday attacked the village of Bijela 
in the Konjic municipality in northern Herzegovina, and engaged 
in sporadic provocations along the entire front between 
Nevesinje and Mostar, the local Bosnian Serb Army command 
informs. Moslems have also been opening fire from a 20-mm gun 
and a heavy machinegun on Serb positions in Sarajevo's suburb of 
Ilidza. 
  Three Moslem snipers have been firing from the city's 
Dobrinja locality at the Serb residential area near Sarajevo 
airport. Moslems have been opening fire also from small-arms and 
hand-held rocket launchers in the area of the Vrbanja bridge. 
  Movements of Moslem troops and mechanisation have been 
reported from the direction of Mt Igman towards the suburb of 
Hrasnica, and from Butmir airport to Donji Kotorac, all in 
Sarajevo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

