<H3> <TI>   Serbs Say Muslims Using Chemical Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Say Muslims Using Chemical Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505124294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1146 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1505124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Zvornik, Bratunac, 15 May (TANJUG) -- In their 
attacks on some areas in the republic of Srpska [in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina] Muslim units have once again used chemical 
weapons, representatives of the VRS [army of the republic of 
Srpska] said today. Serb defensive positions on Mount Majevica 
and in Mala, Velika Jelaca, and Lisaca have been attacked by 
Muslims using shells filled with chlorine-based chemicals. In 
their attacks on Serbs from the Tuzla area Muslim units used 
chemicals on several occasions, although international 
conventions prohibit the use of such weapons. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

