<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Returns to Positions in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Returns to Positions in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305210794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the basis of the agreement on the 
demilitarization of the three-kilometer exclusion zone east of 
the River Drina, the command of the eastern Bosnian operational 
zone of the Bosnia-Herzegovina army in Gorazde has witdrawn its 
troops from the area of Mala Bisernica. Within the 24-hour 
deadline, members of our army withdrew while members of the army 
of the so-called republic of Srpska, who were supposed to 
withdraw all their forces, failed to do so. Positions in Mala 
Bisernica are under the control of UN Protection Force 
[UNPROFOR] troops. Given that the aggressors failed to withdraw 
their (?police), the Bosnia-Herzegovina army returned to its 
positions. 

</TEXT>

