<H3> <TI>   Serbian Attacks on Zvornik Area Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Attacks on Zvornik Area Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505175094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1505175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The free territory of Zvornik has been under 
fierce attack by the aggressor, but our soldiers are scoring new 
successes. 
  [Reporter] After the aggressor's unsuccessful attempts to 
break through our defense lines in the Majevica part of the 
front, soldiers of the 206th Gallant Brigade, aided by soldiers 
from Teocak, have captured important hills of Domanica Kosa, 
Ikovi and Suha Cesma, and are in the immediate vicinity of the 
TV relay station. [passage omitted] 
  Brave soldiers of the 206th Gallant brigade successfully 
repulsed all attacks and inflicted high losses in human lives on 
the chetniks. The remaining chetniks withdrew in panic, leaving 
scores of their dead behind. Unable to shift the defense lines 
to their advantage, the chetniks vented their frustration by 
firing from all available weapons on the free territory, 
destroying whole buildings in Vitinica, (Cakula), Medjedja, 
(Kobilici), Kraljevici, (Nezuk), and Zaseok. Some 1,000 highly 
destructive shells fell on these locations, causing vast 
material damage. Some civilians were killed and wounded. 
Despite all this, our defense lines are firm and stable. This 
was a report from Zvornik by the information service of the 
206th Gallant Brigade. 

</TEXT>

