<H3> <TI>   `Discrimination' Against Non-Muslims Questioned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Discrimination' Against Non-Muslims Questioned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1305175894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1305175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In connection with the announcement issued by the 
cabinet of Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Presidency of the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, that aid in the amount of 100 
German marks will soon be given to all families of killed Muslim 
fighters [sehit] in Bosnia-Herzegovina, the Liberal Party of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina has issued the following statement: 
  We are very pleased with President Izetbegovic's statements 
and concrete activities concerning the welfare of families of 
killed fighters and (?killed Muslim fighters), as well as his 
statement that he will soon devote his endeavors to this problem 
alone. However, what has been left unclear is whether there was 
an error in the announcement or whether discrimination against 
killed fighters, patriots in the defense of the state of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, is really being introduced, something that 
we cannot support. We expect the error, be it in the 
announcement or intentional, to be immediately corrected. 

