<H3> <TI>   U.S. Asked To Support UNPA Reintegration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Asked To Support UNPA Reintegration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1405185394 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 
GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1405185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] In Geneva, Croatia has submitted a request to the 
United States to lend its support in speeding up the process of 
the reintegration of UN Protected Areas [UNPA's] into Croatia. 
During a meeting with US Secretary of State Warren Christopher, 
Minister Granic asked the U.S. Government to lend its firm 
support in the case of Croatia's borders. The meeting took 
place in the UN embassy in Geneva before the formal ceremony 
held to mark the Croat-Muslim agreement. Ministers Granic and 
Christopher talked about the situation in the UNPA and about 
bilateral relations. After a cooperation agreement was reached 
they stressed a need for more specific agreements between 
Croatia and the United States in the future. 
  [Begin Granic recording] One of the important topics was 
U.S. 
support to the Republic of Croatia regarding an approach to the 
international financial institutions, more specifically, the 
credits of the World Bank [word indistinct] the European Bank 
for Reconstruction and Development. [passage omitted] 

