has increased by 3.4 per cent in April, compared to March, 
Yugoslav Prime Minister Radoje Kontic said today. He told 
reporters that the production level in March was almost equal to 
the average level last year, which means that the April increase 
in production indicates an increase in relation to the level 
last year. [sentence as received] 

