<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kaczynski Elected Chairman of Center Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kaczynski Elected Chairman of Center Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1405180794 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1400 
GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1405180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] By 281 votes for to three against, Jaroslaw 
Kaczynski was elected chairman of the Center Alliance during the 
Third Congress of the party, which began in Warsaw today. 
Kaczynski has been party leader since 1990. I expected to be 
elected, but I cannot hide my surprise and emotion. I consider 
the election to be something extraordinary, he said. It puts me 
under the obligation to carry on with the difficult task of 
uniting the center-right, Kaczynski told the delegates, who sang 
to him "May You Live a Hundred Years." 
  Jaroslaw Kaczynski and guests invited to the congress talked 
about the future of the center-right, which aims at building a 
new Poland, efficient and law-abiding and with an economy that 
will open up opportunities for millions of Poles. 
  The congress is attended by the leaders of the parties 
making 
up the Alliance for Poland confederation: Wieslaw Chrzanowski, 
National Christian Union; Romuald Szeremietiev, Movement for the 
Republic; and Kazimierz Michal Ujazdowski, Conservative 
Coalition. 

</TEXT>

