<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Christopher Informs Izetbegovic of U.S. Stance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Christopher Informs Izetbegovic of U.S. Stance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1405211994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1405211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, has had a telephone conversation 
with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. Christopher 
called President Izetbegovic to inform him about the U.S. 
standpoint on the resolution of the situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The United States believes the Bosnian side 
will not miss this opportunity for peace and that a solution can 
be found in the plans put forward by the international 
community's contact group for Bosnia-Herzegovina. President 
Izetbegovic reiterated our resolve to persevere with the peace 
process and said that the Bosnian side was very clear on this 
subject and that at the same time, it also demanded respect for 
the vital interests of Bosnia-Herzegovina as a unitary state. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

