<H3> <TI>   Rugova: Party Will Continue Work if Banned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rugova: Party Will Continue Work if Banned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305113994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1037 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, 13 May (TANJUG) -- President of the 
Democratic Alliance of Kosovo (DSK) Ibrahim Rugova said today 
that his party would continue its activities despite 
announcements that it would be outlawed. At a news conference 
Rugova described as "a provocation" the statement by the head of 
Kosovo district Milos Simovic that the authorities should ban 
the DSK for failing to register. He warned that this could be 
"a dangerous move" and that such a decision "would not be taken 
lightly by the international democratic public." Rugova claims 
that his party was registered in the former SFRY, that it was in 
possession of valid registration documents, and stressed that it 
would continue its work even if banned. 

</TEXT>

