<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister on Cooperation With Baltics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister on Cooperation With Baltics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305160894 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1200 
GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Minister of National Defense Piotr 
Kolodziejczyk, military cooperation between Poland, Germany, and 
other Baltic states is very good. Kolodziejczyk is paying a 
visit to Germany at the invitation of German Minister of Defense 
Volker Ruehe. The talks are also being attended by Danish 
Defense Minister Hans Haekkerup. 
  The Polish defense minister announced that it was agreed to 
include Finland in cooperation, which has joined Partnership for 
Peace, and also Lithuania, Latvia and Estonia. He said that the 
first step would be a military exercise of sapper units, planned 
for October in Jutland and to be attended, among others, by the 
Lithuanians. At Denmark's request, the Poles will provide them 
with logistics. 

</TEXT>

