<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the last experts meeting about the Pact of 
Stability in Athens, Slovakia succeeded in pushing through its 
demands. This has created conditions to enable the Pact of 
Stability to become a suitable platform for the implementation 
of the foreign policy interests of Slovakia. This was said by 
Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik in an interview given to the Press 
Agency of the Slovak Republic in connection with the preparation 
of his official visit to France, where he is to discuss, among 
other things, this initiative. Prime Minister Moravcik envisages 
that, at this stage, the drafting of the documents for the Pact 
of Stability is acceptable to Slovakia. In this connection, he 
stressed that the pact unequivocally respects and promotes the 
principle of the inviolability and immutability of borders. 

