<F P=103> LD1505171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A two-day session of the first congress of the 
Communist Party of Slovakia [KSS] ended in Levice today with the 
adoption of final documents. The party's policy reaffirms that 
the KSS is a Marxist party, the objective of which is to build 
socialism, a democratic society with political and economic 
plurality, a society that would be self-administered, 
prosperous, and socially just. The party's policy says that if 
this party fails to win a partner for a joint course of action, 
it will go into the elections as an independent political 
entity. The delegates reelected Vladimir Dado as KSS chairman, 
and (Ladislav Jaco) was elected KSS central secretary. 

</TEXT>

