<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Imports Exceeded Exports; Slovak Foreign </F>
Trade With European Countries in March"] 
  [Excerpts] Bratislava--Within the framework of foreign 
trade relations with European countries, the Slovak Republic 
exported goods worth 13,587.499 million Slovak korunas [Sk] in 
March 1994 (a total of Sk38,981.804 million for the first three 
months of the year on aggregate) and imported goods worth 
Sk14,052.177 million (Sk42,876,151 for the first three months). 
  The Czech Republic was in first place in terms of the Slovak 
Republic's trade volume with European countries. In March, 
exports to the Czech Republic accounted for 38.58 percent of all 
Slovak exports and 29.41 percent of all Slovak imports. Second 
place is held by Germany, where Slovakia exported 15.76 percent 
of its global exports in March and from which it imported 11.71 
percent of all of its imports. The European country with the 
third-largest trade exchange with Slovakia is Austria; Slovak 
exports to Austria represent 5.40 percent of global Slovak 
exports and 5.90 percent of all Slovak imports. The above 
information was provided by Jaromir Kalincak, director general 
of the Central Customs Administration of the Slovak Republic. 
[passage omitted] 


