<F P=106> [Interview with Defense Minister Pavol Kanis by "(vg)"; </F>
place and date not given: "One Question for Defense Minister 
Pavol Kanis"] 
  [Text] [Correspondent] The UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Forces] command has shown an interest in dispatching another 400 
of our troops to the former Yugoslavia. How will the Slovak 
side react? 
  [Kanis] Naturally, we have to look at all of the aspects of 
this request. It is necessary to weigh the material and 
financial aspects and also, of course, the possibilities for the 
human resources the Slovak Army has at its disposal. However, 
from the preliminary discussions the members of the delegation 
have had among themselves, it is clear that it would be possible 
to comply with the request--on condition that the UN payments 
would not be delayed, as is the case now, by a year, but would 
be made immediately or, possibly, with a slight delay. In this 
case, we could overcome the problem of this department's tight 
budget. 

</TEXT>

