<H3> <TI>   Serbs Fire at UN Near Maglaj; NATO Responds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Fire at UN Near Maglaj; NATO Responds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605144194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1605144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hajrudin Sermic from Maglaj] </F>
  [Text] This morning the Mt. Ozren chetniks, together with 
their recently arrived reinforcements, intensified their attacks 
on the free Maglaj territory. Fierce artillery fire directed at 
the positions of the 201st Chivalrous Brigade on the northern 
parts of the front, near Bijela Ploca, (Kojundzevaca), and 
Haluge started just after 0700 and went on until midday. Tanks, 
Bofors, and mortars from the infamous strongholds on Mt. Ozren 
fired at the town center. Two people were lightly wounded. 
  The UN Protection Forces in Maglaj again came under attack 
this morning, and the blue helmets were again -- for the second 
day running -- forced to respond to the chetnik fire. This 
time, however, NATO planes appeared very quickly. The Serbian 
aggressor is continuing to concentrate his forces toward Maglaj, 
so new attacks on this part of the free Bosnia-Herzegovina 
territory appear imminent. 

</TEXT>

