<H3> <TI>   Serbs Suffer `Total Defeat' on Mt. Majevica </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Suffer `Total Defeat' on Mt. Majevica </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605190294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1605190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by the Press Center of the 206th Chivalrous Brigade </F>
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army from the Zvornik front] 
  [Text] Since early morning the aggressor has been pounding 
the entire Zvornik free territory with tanks, howitzer 
batteries, and mortar batteries of all calibers. At the same 
time on the Mt. Majevica section of the front, the aggressor has 
been trying in vain with combined artillery and infantry attacks 
to break through our newly established defense lines. The brave 
fighters of the 206th Chivalrous Brigade of Zvornik, commanded 
by Commander Semsudin Muminovic, have rapidly and effectively 
repulsed a number of infantry attacks by Karadzic's cutthroats, 
defying a maelstrom of shells that has been raining down on them. 
  The chetniks seem incapable of understanding that they have 
suffered a total defeat on the peaks of Mt. Majevica, and are 
constantly launching new infantry attacks, ignoring the bodies 
of dozens of their fellow fighters that will forever remain on 
these peaks. 

</TEXT>

