<F P=102>   AU1605190194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1605190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After fierce fighting on the Kladanj front, the 
free territory of Bosnia-Herzegovina has been expanded by 32 
square kilometers. Sabotaging the plans of chetnik generals 
Milovanovic and Krstic, the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army fighters 
smashed the Chetnik offensive and penetrated deep into the 
occupied territory toward Zeravica and Vlasenica. Our units 
have progressed to the line of (Sokoli), [words indistinct], and 
(Bijela Stijena). All attempts by the Chetniks to recapture the 
lost territory have been in vain. 
  Over 100 chetniks were killed in this fighting, 20 of whom 
were [word indistinct], and the number of the wounded is several 
times higher. The result of this operation is two tanks, two 
mobile antiaircraft weapons, two 105-mm howitzers, and one 
antiaircraft gun destroyed. The chetnik units in this region 
have been completely smashed, and the volunteers from Serbia are 
fleeing to where they came from in the first place. 

</TEXT>

