<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Civilians Panic as Tuzla Shelled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Civilians Panic as Tuzla Shelled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605161094 Paris AFP in English 1554 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1605161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Tuzla, Bosnia-Herzegovina, May 16 (AFP) -- Two 
heavy artillery shells hit a residential area of the mainly 
Moslem industrial town of Tuzla on Monday [16 May], causing 
panic as residents fled the streets, witnesses said. [passage 
omitted] The shells crashed in mid-afternoon not far from the 
town's hotel, which had been hit Sunday night by a large-calibre 
shell, and left two craters in a children's play area. 
Residents of the town immediately fled the streets, bathed in 
early summer sunshine, to take shelter, dragging their children 
away from play. No injuries were reported. It was the third 
day in succession the northeastern Bosnian town had been 
shelled, apparently from Serb positions some four kilometres 
(2.5 miles) to the north east. Last Wednesday two people were 
killed and four injured in two waves of shelling, prompting 
local authorities to close schools. A decision was to be made 
later Monday on when to reopen them. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

