<H3> <TI>   Turkish Party Protests Treatment of Minority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Party Protests Treatment of Minority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605200194 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1605200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Turks Without Representative in </F>
Constitutional Court"] 
  [Text] Referring to the fact that no judge in the 
Macedonian Constitutional Court is of Turkish origin, the 
Democratic Party of Turks in Macedonian [FYROM -- Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia] issued a public protest and 
condemn of the politics of double standards. Although the Turks 
present a constitutive and constructive element of Macedonia's 
statehood, this act is a repeated attempt to leave this minority 
at the margins of the political life in the country, the party 
announcement says. Such behavior results in distrust for the 
government bodies and institutions. The announcement concludes 
this kind of democracy leads nowhere. 

</TEXT>

