<H3> <TI>   `No Threat' Following Zhirinovkiy's Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `No Threat' Following Zhirinovkiy's Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605135894 Prague DENNI TELEGRAF in Czech 10 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1605135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague DENNI TELEGRAF </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "kos": "Response Is Not Necessary; There Is No </F>
Imminent Danger From Russia"] 
  [Text] Prague--The Interior Ministry closely follows 
developments in Russia, but the present signs do not warrant any 
hasty response. Interior Ministry spokesman Subrt said this 
yesterday. It was his reply to the question of whether the 
Interior Ministry is preparing some measures after the comments 
by Vladimir Zhirinovkiy about an "entirely new regime" in Russia 
before the fall. According to Subrt, our side must wait for the 
official comments and conduct of the legitimate Russian 
Government. "We are all aware of Mr. Zhirinovkiy making very 
strong statements now and then," Subrt said and added that "at 
the moment, there is no threat." 

</TEXT>

