<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Churkin on Withdrawal Deadline for Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin on Withdrawal Deadline for Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605173794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After visiting Russian troops serving with the UN 
Protection Forces in Sector East, Russian Ambassador to Croatia 
Leonid Kerestedziyants told reporters that they discussed the 
implementation of the Zagreb agreement and agreed that the 
Croatian Army must withdraw the remaining weapons by 1600 
tomorrow and the Serbian side must do the same by 2400 tomorrow. 
  The Zagreb agreement has to be fully implemented in all 
protected areas by 2400 tomorrow, the Russian ambassador said. 
If this does not happen further steps will be taken by both the 
Russian and U.S. embassies and the European Union, for what has 
been signed has to be respected. This is not a piece of paper 
which has been signed and can then be forgotten, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

