<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 16 May (PAP)--An intergovernmental agreement 
on "cooperation and exchange of information on some issues 
concerning defense" was signed today by Swedish Defense Minister 
Anders Bjorck and Poland's National Defense Minister Piotr 
Kolodziejczyk. 
  Poland is the first country of the East bloc with which 
Sweden has signed such an agreement. Minister Bjorck pointed 
out that this transpires from the fact that Poland stands "in 
the forefront of the states of this part of Europe that have 
carried out democratic changes." 
  So far, Poland has signed 21 agreements on military 
cooperation, among others, with all of its neighbors. 

