<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Annual Inflation Falls to 9.2 Percent in Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Annual Inflation Falls to 9.2 Percent in Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605200294 Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Czech 11 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1605200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "rum": "The Annual Level of Inflation Continues </F>
To Decline"] 
  [Text] Overall consumer prices, expressing the 
inflationary development, rose by 0.4 percent in April in 
comparison with the preceding month. Czech Statistical Office 
Spokesman J. Lehnerova announced this yesterday. 
  Prices of services, food, and nonfood products each 
increased 
by the same 0.4 percent. Public catering prices recorded the 
greatest increase in April--0.6 percent. Among food products, 
chocolate and sweets showed the largest increase--2.8 to 5.5 
percent. On the other hand, the price of eggs fell by 5.3 
percent. Among the services, cinema and theater seats and 
municipal transport fares rose by more than 2 percent. 
  Total inflation over the four months of this year reached 
2.8 
percent and thus corresponds to government expectations and the 
Czech National Bank's estimates. The annual level of inflation 
is declining as the year progresses. It was 9.2 percent in 
April, down 0.2 percent from March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

