<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Amendments to Election Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves Amendments to Election Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605181694 Bratislava SME in Slovak 11 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1605181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SME </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "so": "Government Approved Bill on Bilingual </F>
Signs"] 
  [Excerpt] Bratislava--[passage omitted] At its meeting 
yesterday, the government agreed with the proposal submitted by 
a group of deputies to amend the law on elections to the Slovak 
National Council. The draft amendment does not change the basic 
principles of the existing legislation governing elections to 
the National Council of the Slovak Republic--the electoral 
system and the size and number of constituencies remain 
unchanged. The proposed amendment mainly clarifies provisions 
pertaining to the organization of elections. According to the 
draft, voters will receive the ballots at the polling 
stations--that is, the ballots will not be delivered to their 
homes. A citizen of the Slovak Republic who is not a permanent 
resident of the Slovak Republic will be entered in the voters' 
register on entering the polling station by the district 
electoral commission, and the commission will record this entry 
in the voter's travel document. When casting the ballot, the 
voter must have his citizenship recorded in his identity papers. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

