<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   MSZP-SZDSZ Foreign Policy Previewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSZP-SZDSZ Foreign Policy Previewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805101394 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0900 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] If they come to power, the Socialists and the Free 
Democrats will conduct a foreign policy which gives equal 
priority to relations with the East and the West and with 
Hungarians living beyond the country's borders. Laszlo Kovacs 
and Istvan Szent-Ivanyi, foreign policy experts for the 
Hungarian Socialist Party [MSZP] and the Alliance of Free 
Democrats [SZDSZ], respectively, have announced that Hungarian 
foreign policy will change substantially both in its style and 
methods. 
  The SZDSZ politician also said that with respect to 
neighboring countries, they will present a pragmatic policy 
which is adjusted to Hungary's dimensions and true significance. 

</TEXT>

