<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HDZ Insists on Dismissing Assembly Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HDZ Insists on Dismissing Assembly Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705122594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At about 1300 the Croatian Assembly's House of 
Counties continued its work following three breaks and a meeting 
of the chairmen of the deputies clubs. The deputies are still 
debating the agenda. Throughout the session the Croatian 
Democratic Union [HDZ] club of deputies explicitly demanded that 
all issues on the agenda be dropped except for the one relating 
to a proposal to recall House of Counties Speaker Josip Manolic. 
  The opposition representatives held a different view. They 
insisted on the original agenda, including the current affairs 
hour during which government representatives were to answer 
questions raised by deputies. The vice president confirmed that 
the government was in agreement with the demand of the HDZ club 
of deputies and that it had withdrawn all parts of the draft 
legislation included in the agenda. 
  During the debate the president of the House of Counties 
called on Vice President Damir Zoric to preside over the rest of 
the session. In conclusion, 12 assembly committees are 
preparing tomorrow's session of the Croatian Assembly Chamber of 
Representatives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
